First rewrite the expression with an exponential:

x^{1/\ln x} = e^{\ln\!\bigl(x^{\,1/\ln x}\bigr)}
            = e^{(1/\ln x)\,\ln x}
            = e^{1}
            = e.

Thus the quantity is identically e for every x > 0 (x≠1), so in particular

lim_{x→∞} x^{1/\ln x} = e.
